h(A,B)
h
\implies h(A_1,B_1) = h(A_2,B_2) \iff (A_1 mod c, B_1 mod d) = (A_2 mod c, B_2 mod d)
\iff A_1 \equiv A_2 mod c
A_2 \equiv B_2 mod d
h[ (A_1,B_1) + (A_2,B_2) ] = h(A_1,B_1) + h(A_2,B_2).
LHS = h[ \; (A_1 + A_2, B_1 + B_2) \; ] = (A_1 + A_2 \mod c, B_1 + B_2 \mod d) 
 = (A_1 \mod c, B_1 \mod d) + (A_2 \mod c, B_2 mod d) = RHS
